<!-- ═══ IMAGERY ═══ -->
<section id="imagery">
  <div class="section-header">
    <div class="section-number">5.0</div>
    <div class="section-title-block">
      <div class="section-eyebrow">Photography &amp; Imagery</div>
      <h2 class="section-title">Image Direction</h2>
    </div>
    <div class="doc-info">Contorno Brand Guidelines<br>Section 5.0: Imagery</div>
  </div>

  <!-- Intro + Do/Don't -->
  <div class="img-intro-grid fi">
    <div class="img-intro-left">
      <p>Contorno photography lives in the tension between documentation and poetry. Images should feel like they were taken by someone who actually loves the place — not by a photographer hired for a shoot. Grain is allowed. Imperfection is allowed. Cliché is not.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="img-do-dont">
      <div class="do-block"><h4>Do</h4><ul><li>Film grain &amp; natural light</li><li>Real moments, unstaged</li><li>Architecture without people</li><li>Graphic color overlays</li><li>Hand-drawn annotations</li><li>La Punta light &amp; shadow</li></ul></div>
      <div class="dont-block"><h4>Don't</h4><ul><li>Overproduced editorial</li><li>Stock photography</li><li>Perfect blue-sky travel</li><li>Heavy retouching</li><li>Generic "luxury hotel" framing</li><li>Posed, artificial subjects</li></ul></div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Treatment 01: Raw / Film -->
  <div class="treatment-seg fi">
    <div class="ts-left">
      <div>
        <div class="ts-num">01</div>
        <div class="ts-title">Raw &amp; Film</div>
        <p class="ts-desc">The foundation of Contorno's visual language. Natural grain, available light, uncropped moments. Architecture photographed as sculpture. People photographed as evidence of life, not lifestyle.</p>
      </div>
      <div>
        <div style="font-size:9px;letter-spacing:.15em;text-transform:uppercase;color:var(--charcoal-light);margin-bottom:8px;">Characteristics</div>
        <div style="font-size:12px;line-height:2.2;color:var(--charcoal-mid);">Film grain · High contrast<br>Natural shadows · Warm tones<br>Imperfect framing</div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="ts-right">
      <div style="display:grid;grid-template-columns:1.6fr 1fr 1fr;grid-template-rows:240px 240px;gap:6px;">
        <div class="mi" style="grid-row:span 2;background:#7a6e5c;padding:0;"></div>
        <div class="mi" style="background:#8a7e6c;padding:0;"></div>
